		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>U. S. Cir Court Clerk&#39;s Office</placeName></p>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>St Paul</placeName> <date>Feby 12&#44; 1863</date>.</p>
				<p><addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir.</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Your letter of <date>2d Feby.</date> With<lb/> rect. for School books and also the Book<lb/> came to hand&#59; I have again to call<lb/> your attention to a little neglect on<lb/> your part&#44; not so much on account of<lb/> the amount&#44; but that matters may be<lb/> properly understood between us.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Soon after I forwarded to you&#44; the<lb/> amount for school books.  I also forwarded<lb/> &#36;3. the amount of my subscription to<lb/> the &#8220;Occident&#8221; for one year and &#36;1.50 for<lb/> 2 Copies of <persName>Dias&#39;</persName> letters&#44; sent to me leaving<lb/> the Bible only in my charge unpaid for</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>did not that letter come safe to hand.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I am sorry to trouble you with this<lb/> small matter&#59; but if I am to attend<lb/> to any business for you it is better that<lb/> we should have all items&#44; properly ac&#45;<lb/>counted for.  I will communicate<lb/> with you hereafter in regard to send&#45;<lb/>ing books here to be disposed of &#38;<lb/> in the meantime will do what I<lb/> can to procure subscribers for you&#44; in<lb/> this section&#44; my time is not so much<lb/> occupied but that I can attend<lb/> to any thing you may desire here&#33;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">The Occident to <persName>Mr Marcuson</persName> and<lb/> myself comes to hand&#33;  <persName>W. M.</persName> I trust<lb/> will content himself here tho&#39; from<lb/> all I have seen of him his great<lb/> fault is being unsettled&#33;  <sic>he</sic> is a<lb/> frequent visitor at my house and</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>both <persName>Rachel</persName> and myself desire a<lb/> great deal of information from in regard<lb/> to Religion in which we both take great<lb/> interest.  <sic>he</sic> is no doubt a very learned<lb/> man&#59; and should be at the head of a<lb/> large congregation&#33;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">We all continue well and <persName>Nelle</persName> quite<lb/> <sic>dilighted</sic> that you should remember&#44;<lb/> her.  I have read the &#8220;Jews &#38; Inquisition<lb/> and with <persName>Mr Marcuson&#39;s</persName> explanaturis<add>&#63;</add>&#44; I have<lb/> been delighted with it&#44; and will cheerfully<lb/> remit the price of any similar work<lb/> you can forward to me.</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)">Yours very Respectfully</p>
			<p rend="indent(9)"><persName role="author">J N Cardoza</persName></p>
				<p><persName>Mr. Abm Elfelt</persName>&#44; is well and sends respects &#38;c</p>
		</body>
